Class CraneException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • java.lang.IllegalStateException
            • de.tuhh.diss.harborstorage.sim.CraneException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class CraneException
extends java.lang.IllegalStateException
    An instance of this class is thrown every time, a PhysicalCrane object does something illegal. Illegal operations are:
    • Try to load or unload the crane while not in loading position
    • Try to load a storage element to a non-empty crane
    • Try to retrieve a storage element from an empty crane
    • Use the store operation on a non-empty storage place
    • Use the store operation while the crane is empty
    • Use the retrieve operation with a non-empty crane
    • Use the retrieve operation on an empty storage place
    • Use the store or retrieve operation while the crane is in an illegal position, that is, a position where no storage place is situated
    If one of these violations occur, this is considered a fatal failure of the system, therefore, this exception class extends the type RuntimeException and therefore must not caught but leads to a halt of the program. A textual description of the problem that occurred is printed to the console.
    Author:
    Weigel / Venzke
